The Confederate States in account comments with Gibs B Johnson 2nd Master Agent on account of the Quartermasters Department at Sherman Texas in the quarter ending on the 31st day of December 1862.
1862, Dec 31 To amount of purchases for Abstract A. $10,456.96 1862, Nov 28th My task received from Major John W Tenimp again $50,000.00
1862, Dec 31 To amount of expeditions for Abstract B    $237.00  
1862, Dec 21 My task received from Major John W Tenimp A2MR $50,000.00
1862, Dec 31 To balance due the Confederate States carried to new account $89306.04
Total $100,000.00  Total $100,000.00
I certify that the above is a true account of all the moneys that have come into my hands on account of the Quartermaster's Department during the quarter ending on the 31st day of Dec, 1862, and that the disbursements have been faithfully made.
Signature: Charles B Johnson 2nd Master Agent

Account Current
4th Quarter. 1862
Chp. B. Johnson
2Mr Agent
at
Sherman Texas
